snippet.textDisplay:
Amusing story: The first time I got in I was 19 years old and it kind of happened by accident. It was my first night during my first ever visit to Berlin. I met up with a friend who had lived there for a few years already and was a regular at Berghain. We initially decided to go to Tresor (a popular somewhat toursity club) as he said there would be no point in trying Berghain. Funnily enough we actually weren't allowed in there because there were "too many guys" according to the bouncer. An odd problem for a club in Berlin.
We decided to get a couple of beers and I convinced my mate to literally just take me to see the building. We stood in the line, chatting, and before we knew it were at the front of the line. Of course, my friend gets nodded in by the assistant bounder and I am separated from him. This dude isn't sure of me so looks to Sven himself - who, on the day was wearing a full red spandex suit. He emerges from the shadow of the door, leaning over on his high stool. Looks me up and down, and nods me in.
In retrospect, I think he wanted to give innocent me some exposure to the hedonism inside. Literally the first thing I saw when reaching the top of the industrial staircase at the back of the main dancefloor was two guys butt naked on top of a podium, having pretty aggressive sex. Once the novelty of these things wears off though, it became an extremely enjoyable, open, and safe environment for me. 
I have been back since then but the place seems a bit less open to these things now. Hardly any nudity inside, whereas the first time I went in 2014 - it was quite common.
